# Unity Editor Shortcuts Skill

When the user asks Unity editor shortcut / hotkey / "how to X faster in Unity" questions, use this reference.

## Rules of the road (read first)

- Shortcuts are **context-sensitive**: most only fire when the matching window is focused (Scene, Hierarchy, Project, Game, etc.). Ask or confirm which window is active.
- Unity has a built-in **Shortcuts Manager**: `Edit > Shortcuts...` on Win/Linux, `Unity > Shortcuts...` on macOS. Teach users to check and rebind here — it also shows every command, even those not listed below.
- The shortcuts below are the **defaults**; if the user's key "does nothing", tell them to check the Shortcuts Manager — their profile may be custom or a package may have claimed the key.
- **macOS mapping**: `Ctrl` → `Cmd`, `Alt` → `Option`. Examples below use Windows naming.

## Transform tools (toolbar)

| Shortcut | Action |
|---|---|
| `Q` | Hand / Pan tool (view) |
| `W` | Move |
| `E` | Rotate |
| `R` | Scale |
| `T` | Rect transform (2D/UI) |
| `Y` | Transform (unified move/rotate/scale) |
| `Z` | Pivot / Center mode toggle |
| `X` | Global / Local rotation mode toggle |
| `V` | Vertex snap (hold while using Move) |
| `Ctrl` (hold while moving) | Grid snap |

